me and link up with it for the return. That way you would not have to carry your return fuel with you on the outboud trip, vastly reducing your initial mass. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomoftenacity>AtomOfTenacity </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/3/03 11:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/atom_of_tenacity.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/16.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re:  Lets Go To Mars</span><hr size=1> You know what’s amazing? We (the US) put all kinds of restrictions on going into space so that private industry cannot get off the ground, give away tens of billions every year to other countries via unconstitutional foreign aid programs and our “public servants” *snickers* turn a deaf ear to our cries for additional  money for space budgets.<br>
